To make api calls!

the server address is http://gmmotto.ddns.net
the app is at /app

to access the database/admin functions, go to
http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/admin
the username is admin and the password is password

to make api calls

example

http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getUserInfo?username=mill1630

that will return a json object representing the info we have for the user.

check out views.py for the list of functions supported, the request.GET.get
are the arguments that we want.

More formal documentation to come.

URL format: 
example call

example
example call
arguments:
	exArg1: whatever 'examplevalue'
	exArg2: whatever 'example another value'

gmmotto.ddns.net/app/example?exArg1=examplevalue&exArg2=example%20another%20value

API calls:

addCourse
adds a course to the course database
arguments:
	name: the name of the course 'CS307'
	title: the title/description of the course 'Software Engineering'
URL example :
http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/addCourse?course_name=CS100&title=programming%20for%20noobs

addInterest
adds an interest to the interest database
arguments:
	name: the name of the interest 'ping pong'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/addInterest?interet_name=bread

addUser
adds a user to the user database
arguments:
	username: the name of the user 'mill1630'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/addUser?username=test

editUser
changes the value of ta particular user
all arguments but username are optional
arguments:
	username: the username of the user 'mill1630'
	year: the year of the user 'FR|SO|JR|SR|GR'
	bio: the bio of the user 'space%20cat%20lover'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/editUser?username=demo&bio=test

getAllUsers:
gets a list of all users, including groups
no arguments
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getAllUsers

getUserList:
gets a list of all users, not including groups
no arguments
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getUserList

getPersonalUserList:
gets a list of all users, excluding a user's blocked users
arguments:
	username: the user whose blocklist is to be used 'mill1630'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getPersonalUserList?username=test

getUserInfo:
returns the object containing the information for a user
arguments:
	username: the username of the user 'mill1630'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getUserInfo?username=test

addUserCourse:
adds a course to a user
arguments:
	username: the username of the user 'mill1630'
	course_name: the name of the course to be added 'CS307'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/addUserCourse?username=demo&course_name=cs280

removeUserCourse:
removes a course from a user
arguments:
	username: the username of the user 'mill1630'
	course_name: the name of the course to be removed 'CS307'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/removeUserCourse?username=test&course_name=cs280

getCourseList:
gets the entire list of courses
no arguments
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getCourseList

addUserInterest:
adds an interest to a user
arguments:
	username: the username of the user 'mill1630'
	interest_name: the name of the interest to be added 'space%20cats'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/addUserInterest?username=test&interest_name=football

removeUserInterest:
removes an interest from a user
arguments:
	username: the username of the user 'mill1630'
	interest_name: the name of the interest to be removed 'bread'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/removeUserInterest?username=test&interest_name=football

getInterestList:
returns a lost of all of the interests in the database
no arguments
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getInterestList

addMessage:
adds a message to the database
arguments:
	sender: the sender username 'mill1630'
	receiver: the receiver username 'abhijay'
	content: the content of the message 'sup%20bby'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/addMessages?p1=demo&p2=test&content=hey

getMessages:
gets the list of messages sent between two participants
arguments:
	p1: the first participant 'mill1630'
	p2: the second participant 'abhijay'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getMessages?p1=demo&p2=test

getOlderMessages:
deprecated

getNewerMessages:
deprecated

getChatList:
gets the list of users a certain user has chatted with
arguments:
	username: the user for whom you want the chat list 'mill1630'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getChatList?user=Test

createGroup:
creates a group
arguments:
	name: name of the group to create 'bbws'
	user: name of the group creator, will be automatically added 'sinnamon'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/createGroup?name=TestingGroup&user=test

addUserToGroup:
adds a user to a group
arguments:
	name: name of the group to add to 'bbws'
	user: username of the user to add 'precious'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/addUserToGroup?name=TestingGroup&user=test

removeUserFromGroup:
removes a user from a group
arguments:
	name: name of the group to remove from 'bbws'
	user: username of the user to remove 'destiny'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/removeUserFromGroup?name=TestingGroup&user=test

getGroupMembers:
gets a list of users in a group
arguments:
	name: name of the group to get the users of 'bbws'
URL examole : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getGroupMembers?name=TestingGroup

sendMessageToGroup:
sends a message to a group
arguments:
	name: name of the group to send the message to 'bbws'
	user: name of the user that is sending the message to the group 'sinnamon'
	content: message to be sent
	'which%20one%20of%20you%20bitches%20used%20my%20flavored%20cocoa%20butter'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/sendMessageToGroup?name=TestingGroup&user=test&content=Hey

getGroupMessages:
returns a list of messages sent to a group
arguments:
	name: name of the group in question 'bbws'
URL example : http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/getGroupMessages?name=TestingGroup

addBlockedUser
adds a user to the block list
arguments:
	username: user to block for 'mill1630'
	block: user to add to block list 'abhijay'
URL example :
http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/addBlockedUser?username=test&block=demo

removeBlockedUser
removes a user from the block list
arguments:
	username: username to unblock for 'mill1630'
	block: user to remove from block list 'abhijay'
URL example: http://gmmotto.ddns.net/app/removeBlockedUser?username=test&block=demo
